# dpkg/apt - List of system packages to install via apt-get during plugin installation.
#
# LoxBerry runs "apt-get install -y <package>" for each non-empty, non-comment line
# in this file. One package name per line. Use the exact package name as you would
# pass it to apt-get on the command line.
#
# This file is processed automatically during installation - you do not need to
# call apt-get yourself in your install scripts.
#
# Only list packages that are not installed by default on LoxBerry (Raspbian/DietPi).
# Unnecessary package installations slow down plugin installation for users.
#
# Examples:
# libwww-perl
# python3-requests
# jq
